adjectives.description: unthawed (comparative more unthawed, superlative most unthawed)

entries.meaning: Which has not been thawed: still frozen.
examples: For a time we struggled on, most intent upon evading the morasses; and staring at every patch of unthawed ice as on a treasure trove, until we reached a rocky knoll, on which we turned and looked downwards, from the bleak uninteresting moor to the dingy, featureless shores.

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of unthaw
